		<h2>Itenerary</h2>
		<h3>What's going on?</h3>
		<p><em>Please note that all these times are just guidelines that your centre may choose to ignore. They're also likely to change without notice.</em></p>
		<h4>Monday</h4>
		<p>On Monday, everyone will arrive and introductions will be made. Once that's over you'll be planning for your big project.
		Coming up with the idea is always the hardest part: don't underestimate it!</p>
		<p>09.30 &mdash; Arriving in the morning</p>
		<p>10.00 &mdash; Coding continues</p>
		<p>13.00 &mdash; Lunch (obviously)</p>
		<p>17.00 &mdash; Let the ideas brew. See you tomorrow!</p>
		<h4>Tuesday - Thursday</h4>
		<p>On Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday, the days will follow a fairly similar format. You'll be planning, learning, coding, designing and possibly
		even wiring away with help from your mentors, alumni and hosts. You may even be joining talks by industry experts from across the country.</p>
		<p>09.30 &mdash; Arriving in the morning</p>
		<p>10.00 &mdash; Coding continues</p>
		<p>13.00 &mdash; Lunch (obviously)</p>
		<p>17.00 &mdash; Remember to sleep! See you tomorrow.</p>
		<h4>Friday</h4>
		<p>Friday morning will be mostly the same as the other days; everyone will meet and get coding as usual. However, at around lunch time
		(this, again, depends on your centre), you'll all be rushing off to the Venue (TBA) for the big night of coding. You may do this with
		your family or with other people in your centre. This is one hue sleepover/camping exercise (approximately 500 participants alone!), hopefully marking
		the finish of your projects.</p>
		<p>09.30 &mdash; Arriving in the morning</p>
		<p>10.00 &mdash; Coding continues</p>
		<p>12.30 &mdash; Lunch time</p>
		<p>13.00 &mdash; Leaving for The Venue (TBA) </p>
		<h4>Saturday</h4>
		<p>On Saturday, you'll wake up in time for the scary bit: the presentations. You'll be presenting to industry experts, other
		participants, parents and other curious people to compete for a place in the afternoon final presentations (the bit with the prizes).</p>
		<p>11.00 &mdash; First presentations begin.</p>
		<p>13.30 &mdash; Lunch is served! </p>
		<p>15.00 &mdash; The big presentation; judges, prizes and other awards.</p>
		<p><em>You may also stay on Saturday night if it helps with transport arrangements.</em></p>
