	<div class="span6 kids-checklists">
		<h2>Checklists</h2>
		<h3>For the Week</h3>
		<p>You'll need to bring with you:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>A laptop &mdash; this can have any operating system or software you like, provided you're comfortable using it. Most of the mentors
			will be using a Mac or Windows PC, so don't bring a Linux (or other) computer if you're not comfortable with coding in it.</li>
			<li>A packed lunch or such &mdash; this is useful for sustinance. Your centre will get in touch with plans in case they've already made arrangements.</li>
			<li>Some programming knowledge &mdash; any amount is useful; the more the better, but don't worry: there'll be people around to help you learn if you're new to it!</li>
			<li>Transport to and from the centre &mdash; again, pretty useful. If there are any problems getting to your local centre, get in touch and we may be able to help. (No promises!)</li>
		</ul>
		<h3>For the Festival of Code</h3>
		<p>You'll need to bring with you:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>A sleeping bag &mdash; more useful stuff</li>
			<li>Funds or some means to get to the site (coordinated by your family or centre)</li>
			<li>You'll still need the laptop from the previous week</li>
			<li>Toiletries and other things you'll need to keep you going for the night and next day</li>
			<li>Your full parents/guardian's contact details (while we're here, make sure they've seen <a href="/parents">the parents section</a>)</li>
			<li>Possibly (dependant on age) your parent or a guardian to come with you. See the parent's section of the website.</li>
		</ul>
